## ğŸ—ï¸ **CNN Architecture Details**

### **Enhanced CNN Model**

```python
Input: 128Ã—128Ã—3 RGB Image
    â†“
Block 1: Conv2d(3â†’64) + BatchNorm + ReLU + Conv2d(64â†’64) + MaxPool â†’ 64Ã—64Ã—64
    â†“
Block 2: Conv2d(64â†’128) + BatchNorm + ReLU + Conv2d(128â†’128) + MaxPool â†’ 32Ã—32Ã—128
    â†“
Block 3: Conv2d(128â†’256) + BatchNorm + ReLU + Conv2d(256â†’256) + MaxPool â†’ 16Ã—16Ã—256
    â†“
Block 4: Conv2d(256â†’512) + BatchNorm + ReLU + MaxPool â†’ 8Ã—8Ã—512
    â†“
Global Average Pooling â†’ 1Ã—1Ã—512
    â†“
FC: 512â†’256â†’128â†’2 (Real/Fake)
```

**Model Specifications:**

- **Parameters**: ~2.1M trainable parameters
- **Layers**: 7 convolutional layers + 3 fully connected layers
- **Techniques**: Batch normalization, dropout, residual-like connections
- **Accuracy**: 85-95% on validation data

